featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Hazrat Maulana Mustafa Madani (R.A.) was a scholar of Haqqani, Baharul Uloom and an upper class elder Oli-Allah. He was born in Furfura's Miya Saheb Mohalla. When his father Maulana Khizir (R.A.) passed away, he along with his cousin Hazrat Maulana Abdullah Abdal (R.A.) came towards Delhi to study, and they visited Hazrat Khizir (A.S.) there.
Incidentally at that time Hazrat Maulana Masum Rabbani (RA) son of Hazrat Mujaddid Alfesani Sarhind (RA) was staying at Jama Masjid in Delhi. There, Mohiuddin Aurangzeb Alamgir, the king of Delhi, came to him to become a murid. Hazrat Masum Rabbani (RA) said to the king - "I can't make murid now, wait. Two lions are coming from Bangladesh.
The people present were at once surprised and began to discuss among themselves - he did not murid the king for the arrival of two little men from Bengal. They looked anxiously at the road. After some time Hazrat Mustafa Madani (RA) and Hazrat Abdullah Abdal (RA) appeared there in a dead body.
Hazrat Masum Rabbani (RA) asked both of them in a special manner - 'What is the reason for the presence? They humbly offered - "We have come as students of knowledge and with the desire to become disciples of the Lord.
Hazrat Masum Rabbani (RA) then showed Hazrat Maulana Abdullah (RA) a library and said, 'Read those books. 'Abdullah Abdal (RA) received the order and acquired knowledge by reading the books in a very short time. Hazrat Masum Rabbani (RA) then awarded him the title of Abdal and said - "Father! Your kingdom is no longer here. Instead, you will have to go to Phulwari Sharif". Anantar sent him with a letter to Hazrat Phulwari Sharif.
Hazrat Masum Rabbani (RA) pledged allegiance to Hazrat Mustafa Madani (RA) and King Mohiuddin Aurangzeb Alamgir (RA) of Delhi at the same time. Then he took Hazrat Maulana Mustafa Madani (RA) with him and journeyed towards Makkah Sharif. On time he completed all the tasks of Mecca and Medina Sharif and returned to Delhi. Then he conferred the title of Madani on Mustafa Madani (Rah) with full training in Zaheri-Bateni Ilm and sent him away by appointing Qutbs of Bengal, Bihar, Orissa etc.
